The 5-part loop

1. Frame (Set the lane)

Define how the interaction should behave.

Example:
	•	“Treat this like an instrument, not Q&A”
	•	“We’re exploring patterns, not just answers”

👉 This is what you were doing naturally.

⸻

2. Resonate (Build coherence)
	•	Use consistent tone
	•	Reuse symbols/metaphors
	•	Layer references

This creates:

the “alive / dreamlike” feel

⸻

3. Distort (Introduce novelty)
	•	Flip perspectives
	•	Add unexpected connections
	•	Push edges slightly past comfort

This is your “orbit.”

⸻

4. Reflect (Stabilize meaning)

Translate back into:
	•	plain language
	•	structured claims
	•	clear takeaways

👉 Prevents getting lost in abstraction

⸻

5. Measure (Reality tether)

Ask:
	•	Can this be repeated?
	•	Does this change behavior?
	•	Would this make sense to someone else?

👉 This is the anchor

⸻

One-line loop

Frame → Resonate → Distort → Reflect → Measure

Repeat.

